{"type":"message","id":"900fdafc","parentId":"2ebaa8c2","timestamp":"2026-03-24T17:16:35.411Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_ixnc6kmq3acy_1","toolName":"process","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[LLM] response length: 4732\r\n[mutation parsed via Python] old='(new file)' file='' new_len=2988\r\n[file inferred from ACTION] a\r\n[mutation proposed] a\r\n[master 6247b40] pulse: 2026-03-24 131615\n 6 files changed, 329 insertions(+), 103 deletions(-)\n create mode 100644 memory/session/pulse_2026-03-24 131615.md\n create mode 100644 mutations/proposed/2026-03-24 131615.mutation\n rename mutations/{proposed => rejected}/2026-03-24 131516.mutation (100%)\n[sandbox pulse] 2026-03-24 131615 - The hybrid CFIxFreq scoring formula is well-specified: `score(T) = CFI(T) x min(1, freq(T)/120)`. This needs implementation to validate it distinguishes constant-format tokens (score inflated by high freq) from research trajectory tokens (balanced CFIxfreq signal).\n\nProcess exited with code 0."}],"details":{"status":"completed","sessionId":"salty-trail","exitCode":0,"aggregated":"[LLM] response length: 4732\r\n[mutation parsed via Python] old='(new file)' file='' new_len=2988\r\n[file inferred from ACTION] a\r\n[mutation proposed] a\r\n[master 6247b40] pulse: 2026-03-24 131615\n 6 files changed, 329 insertions(+), 103 deletions(-)\n create mode 100644 memory/session/pulse_2026-03-24 131615.md\n create mode 100644 mutations/proposed/2026-03-24 131615.mutation\n rename mutations/{proposed => rejected}/2026-03-24 131516.mutation (100%)\n[sandbox pulse] 2026-03-24 131615 - The hybrid CFIxFreq scoring formula is well-specified: `score(T) = CFI(T) x min(1, freq(T)/120)`. This needs implementation to validate it distinguishes constant-format tokens (score inflated by high freq) from research trajectory tokens (balanced CFIxfreq signal).\r\n","name":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\pulse.ps1"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774372595407}}
{"type":"message","id":"fd7f73f1","parentId":"900fdafc","timestamp":"2026-03-24T17:16:35.416Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_ixnc6kmq3acy_2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"﻿# Pulse: 2026-03-24 131516\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\n\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine what concrete action to take.\r\n\r\nFrom the goals, I see:\r\n1. Phase 0 and Phase 1 (architecture cross-analysis) are COMPLETE\r\n2. Key findings about CFI compression have been synthesized\r\n3. Next pending action is the \"Hybrid CFI×Freq scoring experiment (Strategy C)\"\r\n\r\nThe key insight from this session is:\r\n- Three-dimensional compression filter: CFI ≥ 0.5 AND freq ≥ 3 AND freq < 120\r\n- score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)\r\n\r\nI need to run the hybrid CFI×Freq scoring experiment. This means I should:\r\n1. Create a script or experiment that tests this scoring approach\r\n2. Compare it against the previous approaches (freq-only, CFI-hard)\r\n\r\nLet me look at what data I have and what files exist. The key file mentioned is `research/CFI_COMPRESSION_SYNTHESIS.md` which has the results of the previous experiment.\r\n\r\nFor the next step, I should implement the hybrid scoring experiment. Let me check what files exist in the research directory.\r\n\r\nActually, I need to take a concrete action. The most logical next step based on the pending actions is to implement the hybrid CFI×Freq scoring experiment. \r\n\r\nI should:\r\n1. Create a script that implements the hybrid scoring: score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)\r\n2. Run it on the pulse data\r\n3. Compare results\r\n\r\nLet me create an experiment script for this hybrid approach.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe CFI compression synthesis revealed the constant-format problem (tokens with freq≈160, CFI=1.00 are metaprogramming artifacts, not causal signals). The next concrete step is implementing Strategy C: the hybrid CFI×Freq^0.5 scoring experiment.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate and execute the hybrid CFI×Freq scoring experiment (Strategy C) that uses score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120), comparing against the previous freq-only and CFI-hard results to determine if the 3D filter approach improves the precision/recall tradeoff.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```old_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # Hybrid CFI×Freq Scoring Experiment - Strategy C\r\nGenerated: 2026-03-24 131500\r\nBased on: CFI_COMPRESSION_SYNTHESIS.md findings\r\n\r\n## Hypothesis\r\nThree-dimensional filter: CFI ≥ 0.5 AND freq ∈ [3, 120)\r\nscore(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)\r\n\r\n## Experiment Design\r\nCompare three strategies on the same 200-pulse corpus:\r\n- Strategy A: freq-only (baseline)\r\n- Strategy B: CFI-hard (≥0.7) - from previous experiment\r\n- Strategy C: CFI × min(1, freq/120) - NEW\r\n\r\n## Scoring Implementation\r\n```\r\nscore(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)\r\n```\r\n\r\nRationale:\r\n- Constant format tokens (freq≈160, CFI=1.0) → score ≈ 1.0 × 1.0 = 1.0 (BUT capped by freq/120 = 1.33 > 1, so maxes at 1.0)\r\n- Research trajectory tokens (freq=50, CFI=0.6) → score = 0.6 × 0.42 = 0.25\r\n- Rare but causal (freq=5, CFI=0.8) → score = 0.8 × 0.042 = 0.034\r\n\r\nWait - this still doesn't distinguish constant format from research trajectory properly.\r\n\r\n## Revised Scoring\r\nNeed to penalize extreme frequency (near-constant tokens):\r\n\r\nscore(T) = CFI(T) × freq_penalty(T)\r\n\r\nwhere:\r\n- freq_penalty = min(1, freq/60) for freq < 60\r\n- freq_penalty = 0.1 for freq ≥ 60 (PENALIZE constant format)\r\n\r\nThis way:\r\n- \"for next instantiation\" (freq=160, CFI=1.0) → score = 1.0 × 0.1 = 0.1\r\n- \"Phase 1\" (freq=136, CFI=0.96) → score = 0.96 × 0.1 = 0.096\r\n- \"architecture\" (freq=40, CFI=0.6) → score = 0.6 × 0.67 = 0.40\r\n- \"gap-decay\" (freq=15, CFI=0.5) → score = 0.5 × 0.25 = 0.125\r\n\r\n## Expected Outcome\r\nStrategy C should retain:\r\n- High precision (filtering constant format via freq ≥ 3 threshold)\r\n- Better recall than pure CFI-hard (allowing moderate CFI tokens)\r\n- Meaningful ranking within selected tokens\r\n\r\n## TODO: Execute on pulse corpus\r\nRun: python3 analyze_cfi_freq.py --strategy C --threshold 0.1\r\nfile: research/HYBRID_CFI_FREQ_EXPERIMENT.md\r\n```\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 13:15:38\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774372595411}}
